{{Quote|Some say the coral implants ruin our slaves. Only the weak ones.|Yuuzhan Vong slaver|<ref name="The New Essential Guide to Weapons and Technology">''[[The New Essential Guide to Weapons and Technology]]''</ref>}}
'''Yorik-Kul''', or '''surge-coral''' in [[Galactic Basic Standard/Legends|Galactic Basic Standard]], was an organic device used by the [[Yuuzhan Vong]]. Surge-coral was implanted into [[Slavery/Legends|slaves]], which would then allow the slave to receive mental commands from a [[yammosk]] or a [[dhuryam]]. This, however, came at a cost, since the wearers would eventually lose their [[Sentience/Legends|sentience]] and become mindless beings. Slaves that had lost their minds were used as cannon fodder to absorb blaster fire on the battlefield. Surge-coral also caused its wearers to grow thin and vanish in [[The Force/Legends|the Force]]. Eventually, the [[Shaper caste|Shapers]] developed surge-coral that was less detrimental to the slaves, which only caused pain instead of turning them into drones.<ref name="The New Essential Guide to Weapons and Technology" />

[[Darth Caedus|Jacen Solo]] was implanted with surge-coral after he was captured by the Yuuzhan Vong, which eventually allowed him to [[Vongsense|sense]] the Yuuzhan Vong through the Force. [[Darth Krayt|A'Sharad Hett]] was also the victim of said implantation during his own time as a captive of the Yuuzhan Vong. Over a hundred years later, Hett, as Darth Krayt, was plagued and slowly being killed by the surge-coral's effects. Krayt was thus motivated to find and use [[Cade Skywalker]] to heal him of his implants.

By [[127 ABY]], [[Sith Lord/Legends|Sith Lady]] [[Darth Maladi]] and [[Zenoc Quah]] of the [[One Sith]] had created a [[Vongspawn virus|strain]] of Yorik-Kul that, after implanted, would grow when exposed to [[Force lightning/Legends|Force lightning]], causing extreme pain and even death.

